The paper deals with the task of rule mining over large knowledge bases, which involves techniques from databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a parallel incremental rule mining framework that efficiently mines rules based on the relational model and applies updates to large knowledge bases. The paper also applies multiple optimization techniques to reduce runtime, which involves distributed computing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.DC.
